### 7.3 Intended Use
**Approved Uses:**
- Academic research on satellite anomaly detection
- Algorithm development and benchmarking
- Educational purposes

**Prohibited Uses:**
- Operational satellite control without further validation
- Mission-critical decisions without human oversight

---

## 8. Data Limitations

### 8.1 Known Limitations
1. **Synthetic Data:** Generated data may not capture all real-world complexities
2. **Limited Anomaly Diversity:** Finite set of anomaly types compared to operational reality
3. **Stationary Assumptions:** May not reflect long-term mission degradation
4. **Simplified Physics:** Simulation may use simplified thermal/power models

### 8.2 Recommended Improvements
- Incorporate more diverse anomaly scenarios
- Validate with real mission data if available
- Extend temporal coverage to multiple years
- Include seasonal variations (e.g., eclipse seasons)

